async: This option prevents the plugin from polling to check if the deployment is complete across all pods. It speeds up the deployment process as the plugin doesnâ€™t have to wait for confirmation from all pods.
clean: When the clean option is used, the plugin deletes the entire proxy or sharedflow. This is helpful when you want to remove an existing deployment completely.
inactive: This option imports the proxy or sharedflow without activating it. The proxy/sharedflow is imported into the Apigee environment but will not be active and serving traffic until explicitly activated.-->
                <apigee.googletoken.email>${googleTokenEmail}</apigee.googletoken.email> <!-- Available in Apigee X and Apigee hybrid 1.6 + 
